assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Senkon Logistics Co., Ltd. provides various logistics services in Japan. The company offers third party logistics services; general cargo, precision mechanical equipment, and vehicle transport services; and industrial waste collection and transportation services, as well as owns warehouses, including location management, low-temperature, agricultural tool, tire, electronic appliance, general, electronic component, open-air yard, and information warehouses, as well as trunk room facilities. It also provides document and personal data management services; moving services, including packing/unpacking, piano transportation, room cleaning, computer and vehicle transportation, disposal collection, plant machinery transportation, and AC installation/de-installation services; and international intermodal logistics services through land, sea, and air transportation. In addition, the company offers civil engineering, construction, architectural designing, construction supervision, and related services, as well as automobile disassembly and maintenance services. Further, it engages in the custom broker, real estate and insurance agency, and general worker dispanching businesses; selling of new and used cars; planning, development, maintenance, and sales of software; and production, processing, import, export, and sale of agricultural and fishery products. Additionally, the company offers composite materials based on wood and plastic; generates and supplies natural energy power; and collects and sells rocks, stone, soil, gravel, sand, etc. It also undertakes removal of radioactive material works, as well as sells apparatus for removing radioactive material; and provides medical products. Senkon Logistics Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 1959 and is headquartered in Sendai, Japan.
